            <div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">
                
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">This is the year</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> of Kōpparakesarivarman who has taken <supplied reason="lost">Madu</supplied>rai; <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> the gold from the houses <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>maṉaip poṉṉum</foreign></supplied> and the gold from the fines <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>taṇṭap poṉṉum</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vacca </foreign>, that is, <foreign>vaitta</foreign></supplied> thirty <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>muppatu</foreign></supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible"><foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign>s</supplied> of gold <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>poṉ</foreign></supplied> for four <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nāl</foreign></supplied> forehead-plates <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>paṭṭam</foreign></supplied><note>Alternatively: thirty four gold coins for three / tirthy ... forehead plates.</note> <gap reason="lost"/></p>
            
